Explanation:
The solution uses two stacks to implement a FIFO queue. The push operation pushes the element onto the first stack (stack1) and then onto the second stack (stack2). The pop operation removes elements from both stacks until stack2 is not empty, then returns the element from stack2. The peek operation is similar to pop but does not remove the element. The empty operation checks if stack2 is empty. The time complexity is O(1) for all operations as the operations are performed on constant-sized stacks. The space complexity is also O(1) as the stacks have a constant size. The energy implications are low as the operations do not consume significant energy.

